The paper deals with coded caching in multi-antenna communication setups, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The focus on subpacketization and cache placement algorithms suggests a potential fit for distributed systems (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's emphasis on achieving maximum degrees of freedom during transmission aligns with the goals of signal processing (cs.SI).
